  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Import your `custom.py` into your project.\r\n\r\n*Don't have it, or it doesn't work? That's ok! Copy the code from* <a href=\"https://studio.code.org/projects/pythonlab/9dJ8tm4IBBuPZGDmBsrCLljUC2VI-79EgkHn6b-r8KQ/view\" target=\"_blank\">***here***</a> *and paste it into a new file in your project.*\r\n\r\n2. In `custom.py`, write the `paint_or_move()` function. Inside this function, use an `if/else` statement:\r\n\r\n   * If the `Painter` has paint, paint the space\r\n   \r\n   * Else, move forward one space\r\n\r\n3. Save `custom.py` to your Backpack.\r\n\r\n4. In `main.py`, import the functions you need and help the `Painter` navigate around The Neighborhood.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/71a82d81a65fdd52f2be35cd4425cae4-choiceD.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nUse `this.painter.has_paint()` in your `if` statement to check if the `Painter` still has paint. If it does, paint the space. If not, move forward to the next one.",
